%% Sequence — driver authentication + nearby offers (NOTE: starred steps are
%% endpoints the mobile app expects that the backend does NOT expose yet —
%% see docs/api-gap-analysis.md).
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Driver
    participant App as Driver App (Expo)
    participant API as FastAPI /v1
    participant SEC as Security (JWT)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Driver->>App: enter +966 5XXXXXXXX
    App->>App: validate Saudi mobile -> E.164
    App->>API: POST /auth/login  (email/password today; OTP planned*)
    API->>SEC: authenticate() + create_access_token(sub, role)
    SEC->>DB: load user, verify hash
    API-->>App: 200 {access_token, user}
    App->>App: store token, signIn(driver)

    Note over App,API: Driver goes online
    App->>API: PATCH /drivers/me {is_available:true}*
    App->>API: GET /shipments/nearby*
    API->>DB: query READY shipments near driver home_warehouse
    API-->>App: 200 [ShipmentRequest]
    App-->>Driver: render dashboard + offers
